<subSubSection id="C3776556ED6A380EFF4DFCB9FE5EFC50" box="[136,411,887,914]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED6A380EFF4DFCB9FE5EFC50" blockId="571.[136,411,887,914]" box="[136,411,887,914]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">
<heading id="D09A81B1ED6A380EFF4DFCB9FE5EFC50" bold="true" box="[136,411,887,914]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFF4DFCB9FE5EFC50" bold="true" box="[136,411,887,914]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFF4DFCB9FEE3FC53" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[136,294,887,914]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Mecodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFF4DFCB9FEE3FC53" bold="true" box="[136,294,887,914]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Mecodelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED6A380EFEE8FCB9FE5EFC50" box="[301,411,887,913]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED6A380EFF4DFC75FD1AFA51" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED6A380EFF4DFC75FD1AFA51" blockId="571.[136,778,955,2070]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFF4DFC75FF3EFC14" bold="true" box="[136,251,955,981]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFEAFFC72FE20FC14" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1859" box="[362,485,956,981]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFEAFFC72FE20FC14" box="[362,485,956,981]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Doropygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like. Prosomal somites divided only by weak constrictions; third and fourth pedigerous somites fused, forming inflated brood pouch. Free urosome clearly 5-segmented, inserted into ventral side of brood pouch. Caudal ramus armed with small setae. Rostrum well-developed. Antennule incompletely segmentedwith reduced setation. Antenna 3-segmented with small terminal claw. Labrum distinct. Mandible consistingof biramous palp only; exopod and endopod fused to basis, lobate, unsegmented, each armed with 4 setae. Maxillule, maxilla and maxilliped each represented by single lobe bearing 1 to few setae. Legs 1–4 biramous with extremely long, unsegmented rami; setation reduced. Leg 5 represented by 2 processes each bearing 1 seta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED6A380EFF78FA56FDD4FA12" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED6A380EFF78FA56FDD4FA12" blockId="571.[136,778,955,2070]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFF78FA56FE7BFA70" bold="true" box="[189,446,1431,1458]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED6A380EFF78FA56FF3DFA73" box="[189,248,1432,1458]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Type</typeStatus>
and only species
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFE09FA59FD17FA70" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[460,722,1431,1457]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Mecodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edentatus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFE09FA59FD17FA70" box="[460,722,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Mecodelphys edentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED6A380EFD1CFA56FEC5FA15" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFD1CFA56FF3CFA15" bold="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">gen. et sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED6A380EFF78FA12FD9EF99A" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED6A380EFF78FA12FD9EF99A" blockId="571.[136,778,955,2070]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFF78FA12FEFBFA37" bold="true" box="[189,318,1500,1526]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Etymology</emphasis>
. The generic name is derived from the Greek 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFF10FA30FED5F9D6" box="[213,272,1534,1559]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">meco</emphasis>
(=long) and - 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFE6AFA33FDC0F9D6" box="[431,517,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">delphys</emphasis>
(a common ending for genera in the family) and refers to the elongate swimming legs of the new genus. Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED6A380EFF78F9AAFB58FEEC" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED6A380EFF78F9AAFB58FEEC" blockId="571.[136,778,955,2070]" lastBlockId="571.[810,1452,173,301]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFF78F9AAFEEFF9BF" bold="true" box="[189,298,1636,1662]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Remarks</emphasis>
. The body of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFE35F9ADFD41F9BC" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[496,644,1635,1661]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Mecodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFE35F9ADFD41F9BC" box="[496,644,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Mecodelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED6A380EFD50F9AAFCCFF9BF" box="[661,778,1636,1662]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFD50F9AAFCC6F9BF" bold="true" box="[661,771,1636,1662]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFE46F948FE2CF95E" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[387,489,1670,1695]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFE46F948FE2CF95E" box="[387,489,1670,1695]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but its mouthparts and legs are entirely different from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFDAAF966FD10F900" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[623,725,1704,1729]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFDAAF966FD10F900" box="[623,725,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other genera in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFE69F904FDD7F922" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[428,530,1738,1763]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFE69F904FDD7F922" box="[428,530,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group. Although the characteristically elongate and unsegmented rami of legs 1–4of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFF17F8C3FEA3F8E6" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[210,358,1805,1831]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Mecodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFF17F8C3FEA3F8E6" box="[210,358,1805,1831]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Mecodelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED6A380EFEAFF8C0FE14F8E9" box="[362,465,1806,1832]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFEAFF8C0FE0EF8E9" bold="true" box="[362,459,1806,1832]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are sharedby 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFDACF8C0FD11F8E6" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[617,724,1806,1831]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Unimeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFDACF8C0FD11F8E6" box="[617,724,1806,1831]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Unimeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED6A380EFD1CF8C0FF7FF88B" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFD1CF8C0FF71F88B" bold="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, they display several other important morphological differences. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFEF9F89CFE15F8AD" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[316,464,1874,1900]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Mecodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFEF9F89CFE15F8AD" box="[316,464,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Mecodelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED6A380EFE18F89CFD88F8AD" box="[477,589,1874,1900]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFE18F89CFD82F8AD" bold="true" box="[477,583,1874,1900]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
the urosome is distinctly 5-segmented whereas it is unsegmented in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFF4DF858FF36F86E" authority="The" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[136,243,1942,1967]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Unimeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFF4DF858FF36F86E" box="[136,243,1942,1967]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Unimeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED6A380EFF38F858FEAFF871" box="[253,362,1942,1968]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFF38F858FEA1F871" bold="true" box="[253,356,1942,1968]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
The mandible of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFDFEF858FD0AF871" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[571,719,1942,1968]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Mecodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFDFEF858FD0AF871" box="[571,719,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Mecodelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED6A380EFD1CF858FF7EF813" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFD1CF858FF71F813" bold="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
lacks the coxal gnathobase and its exopod and endopod are both fused to the basis whereas the mandible of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFF6CF832FED1F7D4" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[169,276,2044,2069]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Unimeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFF6CF832FED1F7D4" box="[169,276,2044,2069]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Unimeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED6A380EFED8F832FE4FF7D7" box="[285,394,2044,2070]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFED8F832FE46F7D7" bold="true" box="[285,387,2044,2070]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a pectinate coxal gnathobase and has a free exopod and endopod. The maxilliped is present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFC5BFF01FBF7FF28" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[926,1074,207,233]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Mecodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFC5BFF01FBF7FF28" box="[926,1074,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Mecodelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED6A380EFBFCFF01FB66FF28" box="[1081,1187,207,233]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFBFCFF01FB58FF28" bold="true" box="[1081,1181,207,233]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
but absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFA85FF1EFA6EFF28" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1344,1451,208,233]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Unimeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
